<item>
            <title>[SPARK-51638] Fetching the remote disk stored RDD blocks via the external shuffle service is not working</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-51638</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-43221&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-43221&lt;/a&gt;, remote fetching of disk-stored RDD blocks is not working.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The getLocationsAndStatus method does not use the external shuffle service when the blocks are not host-local. The fallback to extend the search to all executors only includes the active executors, so after downscaling, blocks stored on a killed executor will not be found there which leads to recompute. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
